WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.340
[Amit Varma]: How should we think about health? Well, here's how I think of my personal health. I don't

00:00:09.340 --> 00:00:14.380
[Amit Varma]: sleep enough. I don't exercise enough. I eat the wrong food. In other words, just because

00:00:14.380 --> 00:00:19.840
[Amit Varma]: I feel okay now, I act as if I don't need to do anything to make sure I feel okay later.

00:00:19.840 --> 00:00:24.620
[Amit Varma]: But one day, I'll fall ill and then I'll be at my doctor's clinic saying kindly give medicines.

00:00:24.620 --> 00:00:29.000
[Amit Varma]: I will be disciplined in taking them. I care about my health. This is the wrong approach.

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:33.800
[Amit Varma]: My thinking about my personal health care is flawed, and I will only realize it when

00:00:33.800 --> 00:00:39.080
[Amit Varma]: I fall ill. And then if I get better, I will forget it again. And that's our nation's attitude

00:00:39.080 --> 00:00:44.060
[Amit Varma]: towards health care, especially if we are among the urbanized English speaking elites.

00:00:44.060 --> 00:00:47.960
[Amit Varma]: We feel okay most of the time. And when we don't, we have access to fancy doctors and

00:00:47.960 --> 00:00:52.980
[Amit Varma]: fancier hospitals. We don't spend time worrying about our health care system. And yet, we

00:00:52.980 --> 00:00:57.940
[Amit Varma]: are now in the middle of a crisis where we can't ignore it anymore. You could say as

00:00:57.940 --> 00:01:02.840
[Amit Varma]: a nation, as a democracy, we are suffering the impact of a chronic disease that we had

00:01:02.840 --> 00:01:08.200
[Amit Varma]: earlier normalized. And it is now making us suffer. COVID-19 has made it clear that our

00:01:08.200 --> 00:01:13.320
[Amit Varma]: health care system is broken. As much as that, it has also revealed that our dysfunctional

00:01:13.320 --> 00:01:17.880
[Amit Varma]: state is a greater crisis than COVID-19. In fact, our dysfunctional state is a chronic

00:01:17.880 --> 00:01:23.960
[Amit Varma]: crisis that we have been suffering from for over 70 years. Now maybe fixing the state

00:01:23.960 --> 00:01:29.020
[Amit Varma]: is beyond us. But we must ask ourselves, how can we fix our health care system? We need

00:01:29.020 --> 00:01:34.520
[Amit Varma]: to do it. And we need to start now before COVID-19 recedes, and we slip back into our

00:01:34.520 --> 00:01:42.880
[Amit Varma]: bubbles of denial. And before we fix it, we need to understand it.

