[Guest]: have an outline but precisely because I think it's evolving so much as we see

00:18:21.720 --> 00:18:26.440
[Guest]: right so India does have an incredible tradition of civil society yeah you know

00:18:26.440 --> 00:18:30.120
[Guest]: there's no shortage of very very well-minded well-motivated sincere

00:18:30.120 --> 00:18:34.600
[Guest]: organizations trying to do a lot of good and I do think there's a lot to be a lot

00:18:34.600 --> 00:18:38.280
[Guest]: to be said now I think the challenge is what I've seen in the space is that

00:18:38.280 --> 00:18:44.640
[Guest]: there is a lot of distributed subscale initiatives right mean that people do in

00:18:44.640 --> 00:18:50.520
[Guest]: different places and thinking about how do you leverage that general angst that

00:18:50.520 --> 00:18:54.720
[Guest]: citizens have that they want to shape their surroundings for the common good

00:18:54.720 --> 00:18:59.120
[Guest]: how do you take that and channel that enthusiasm and desire in some in a

00:18:59.120 --> 00:19:02.080
[Guest]: constructive way so one of the big things that's happened between the last

00:19:02.080 --> 00:19:05.120
[Guest]: podcast and this is like I have gone back and heard so many more of your

