[Guest]: the onion and seeing okay why are these incentives of the individual agents not

00:56:42.120 --> 00:56:46.560
[Guest]: aligned with the macro good and then the third is you know empirics and data and

00:56:46.560 --> 00:56:50.880
[Guest]: causal analysis and causal inference which is in the problem particularly in

00:56:50.880 --> 00:56:54.440
[Guest]: things like health is theoretically I can argue any issue both left and right

00:56:54.440 --> 00:56:58.440
[Guest]: okay so and which is why I think the empirical turn of economics in the past

00:56:58.440 --> 00:57:02.160
[Guest]: 20 years or 30 years has been such a good thing because we're now able to

00:57:02.160 --> 00:57:05.200
[Guest]: take a lot more of this abstract theorizing and come down to brass tacks

00:57:05.200 --> 00:57:07.960
[Guest]: and saying okay now let's look at the actual data and seeing which side do

00:57:07.960 --> 00:57:12.520
[Guest]: these trade-offs go off okay so and that's kind of why economics in any

00:57:12.520 --> 00:57:17.480
[Guest]: policy area right I mean in fact Marty Feldstein you know in my last few years

00:57:17.480 --> 00:57:20.440
